events.1536: First foundation of the city by Pedro de Mendoza.
events.1580: Second foundation of the city around fort built by Juan de Garay.
events.1620: Town becomes capital of Buenos Aires Province.
events.1776: City becomes capital of Viceroyalty of the Río de la Plata.
events.1853: City becomes capital of State of Buenos Aires.
events.1871: Yellow fever epidemic. City fire department established.
events.1880: City separated from Buenos Aires Province; Municipalidad de la Ciudad de Buenos Aires established.
events.1895: Museo Nacional de Bellas Artes opens.
events.1936: Kavanagh Building constructed. Maldonado Stream tubed. Obelisco built.
events.1977: Demonstrations by Mothers of the Plaza de Mayo begin.
events.1987: April: Catholic Pope John Paul II visits city.
events.1992: 17 March: Bombing of Israeli embassy. National Library building inaugurated.
events.1994: 18 July: Bombing of Argentine Israelite Mutual Association building.
events.1996: Autonomous City of Buenos Aires established per 1994 amendment of the Argentine Constitution.
events.1999: Buenos Aires International Festival of Independent Cinema begins.
events.2001: City named World Book Capital by UNESCO.
events.2010: Metrobus begins operating. City named World Book Capital by UNESCO.
events.2012: 22 February: Train crash. 4 April: F2 2012 Buenos Aires tornado.
events.2013: Jorge Mario Cardinal Bergoglio, Cardinal, Archbishop of Buenos Aires, is elected as Pope Francis, succeeding the retired Pope Benedict XVI.
events.2015: 3 June: The feminist movement Ni una menos organizes its first massive demonstrations against gender-based violence, popularising the campaign throughout Argentina and several Latin American countries.
events.2017: Alvear Tower completed as the tallest building in Argentina.
events.2023: A specialized exhibition recognised by the Bureau International des Expositions will be held.
